HEADWORD: Cutinization
<hw>Cu`tin*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(k?`t?n-?-z?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The conversion of cell walls into a material
which repels water, as in cork.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

